## Buildroot

A Buildroot cross-compilation environment was configured on WSL2 Ubuntu targeting AArch64 Cortex-A53. Packages included: Python 3, dropbear SSH, wpa_supplicant, bluez-utils, gpsd, i2c-tools, usbutils.

The resulting rootfs.tar is approximately 51MB uncompressed.

Kernel modules for the H700 (WiFi RTL8821CS, display, Mali GPU) were extracted from a running KNULLI instance over SSH and added to the rootfs at `/lib/modules/4.9.170/`.

The rootfs is packaged as a squashfs image and placed at `/boot/batocera` on the FAT32 boot partition, which is where KNULLI's initramfs expects to find it.

