## Current status

The device powers on and displays the KNULLI bootloader splash screen. The initramfs appears to be loading but something is failing before userspace comes up. The screen stays on the boot splash with no further output.

Diagnosis is blocked by lack of serial console access and no mini HDMI adapter. One has been ordered, arriving tomorrow. Once connected to a monitor the kernel boot log should make the failure immediately obvious.

The most likely causes are an overlayfs mount failure or a missing directory in the rootfs that the initramfs expects.

